threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot
threads.message:
[PLAIN][SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot[/PLAIN]

Hi there,

I have a water damaged 820-3437. I replaced a bunch of corroded components, repaired some traces, and I'm getting a fan spin, but no chime, no display, no boot.

I have all rails present, including VCORE, but the CPU doesn't heat up at all.

I assume I'm looking at a dead CPU here? Or is there something else I might have overlooked?

Thanks in advance,
Bruce

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot
threads.message: Try a donor bios just to check, but double check all your clock / BIOS lines continuities and pullups.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot
threads.message: All signals good out from U1950?

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot
threads.message: Yeah U1950 is a good suspect.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3437 All rails present, fan spins, no display, doesn't boot, CPU not getting hot
threads.message:
Thank you, that's what it was. There was a nice, big, juicy bit of corrosion under pin 8 of U1950. Cleaned up, replaced and it's booting beautifully. The post can be closed now.

This subscription is worth every cent.

Many thanks,
Bruce
